						<p>Slab set up near the Sūryanārayaṇa temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1535 Paridhāvi, (current), Srāvaṇa ba. 10,</hi> corresponding to 1612 A.D., August 11, Tuesday.</p>						

						<p>It states the setting of a Nandi-pillar by Chavaṭa Samgamayya son of Nagābattuḍu.</p>						

